post_text: Great news!!!! Please be sure to complete the survey!
shared_text:
Felicity-Franklin Local School District
September 3 at 2:41 PM ·

Good Afternoon Cardinal Families. I am pleased to share that Felicity Schools has been awarded a Coronavirus Relief Funds – Broadband Ohio Connectivity Grant in the sum of $151,446.00. This grant money is earmarked to provide and/or improve high speed internet access to the families of the district. The district will be purchasing high speed internet equipped iPads, hot spots, and will be expanding the school WiFi outside of the building. Later this afternoon I will be emailing a survey to parents and also posting a link to the survey on the district website. It is extremely important that each family fill out and submit the survey. The district will use the information gathered to determine how to best deploy the new technology. I realize we gathered similar information last spring. However, we want to make sure our information is current and accurate.

Felicity-Franklin Local School District
May 29 at 2:18 PM ·

To all of our kindergarten families and those who love and support them!

Please grab a tissue and click on the link to view the virtual graduation for our kindergarten class of 2020.
http://bit.ly/ffel2020k

Next week, each kindergarten family will receive a CD of the graduation and each kindergarten graduate will receive a t-shirt purchased by our PTO to commemorate this special event. To honor them, our goal is to have a parade through the hallway, with our kindergarten graduates wearing their cap and t-shirt, when we are able to return to the school building in the fall. A special thanks to the parents, kindergarten teachers and Michael Roush for all of the contributions and work on the graduation video. CONGRATULATIONS TO THE KINDERGARTEN CLASS OF 2020! WE ARE SO PROUD OF YOU!!!

Felicity-Franklin Local School District
March 15 at 6:09 PM ·

Many students come to school each day and not only get education, but also access to many other resources including nutritional meals. I’m happy to say that our community is full of good people who are looking to help and support their neighbors. The United Methodist Church in collaboration with FFLSD will be offering to-go meals for students on Tuesdays and Thursdays at 2pm for pick-up only (at the church). Meals will include a to-go breakfast for the following day. The United Methodist Church will continue their Saturday meals for anyone by pick-up only between 11am-1pm as well.

Felicity-Franklin Local School District
October 16, 2018 at 4:21 PM ·

Dear Parents,

A few weeks ago we communicated that we have some confirmed cases of fifth disease at our elementary school. Today we want to let you know that we continue to see additional cases. After consulting with the health department again, we have identified additional measures to limit the spread of this illness. We are taking extra cleaning precautions in the classrooms and common areas of the school. For the next several days we will not allow students to use the water fountains. We will provide water stations for students with cups or students may bring in their own water bottles. Hand washing will continue to be a priority throughout the school day.

As a reminder, if your child has a fever, he or she should be kept at home until fever free for 24 hours. Please contact our school nurse, Mrs. Peron, if you have any questions at 513-362-5354.

Additional information about fifth disease:
https://www.cdc.gov/parvovirusb19/fifth-disease.html

If you have a school-aged student in need of breakfast and lunch this summer, simply text “FOOD” to 877877 and receive a message back with a location closest to where they can get free summer meals.
Please copy, paste, and post!
Even if you aren't in need, someone else's kids are. No child deserves to go hungry, ever.
This is a nationwide program so please repost for all of the children who are struggling to get enough food.

post_text:
Please share!
Felicity-Franklin Elementary is looking for a long-term substitute teacher for our county preschool classroom. The position begins January 10, 2018 and lasts for approximately 4 to 6 weeks. It will be full days 8:00-3:40 Monday-Friday.

A valid special education certification is preferred for this integrated classroom. A valid PK-3 teaching license will be considered. Must have excellent verbal and written communication skills; must be able to work collaboratively with colleagues and staff; must complete and pass BCII and FBI background checks.

Compensation is $92.00/per day

Submit cover letter, resume, and current licensure to Jennifer Keller, Elementary School Principal at kellerj@felicityschools.org or call 513.362.5421. The school address: 105 Market Street Felicity, Ohio 45120.
